The numbers are also stark publican launch of the report, Riama Alhagani, also a representative of the Institute for Security Studies’ Regional Office in Ghana, warned that talk of a gendered peace process in Somalia “does not really enhance the security of women in Somalia.” “What we need is to transform culture spaces to change the negative minds of people who use rituals to cover up their [violation] of rights of women. If the talk [of a gendered peace process] does not address those cultural factors, then we are missing the explanation. We have a hard time trying to understand how we can have a gendered peace process when we don’t have [the] proper education.”
